Came here with my two suite mates for dinner right before the start of classes, and it was so fun! There was no wait to get a table (probably bc it was a Monday night) and the food was so good. We ended up getting two small dishes and one dish to share, and we were all so stuffed at the end. The waiter was very nice to us, and he even offered to take our picture for us. When we came down from the restaurant back to the group floor, the hotel lobby boy gave me his number, which was a little peculiar, but other than that, it was a very fun experience. INSTAGRAM: @FRIDAYSFOODHUNT  I can honestly say that I have enjoyed this restaurant. When I walked in, I had the choice of sitting in or outside. Not sure why people have posted negatively about this restaurant and bar, but I can only write about what my experience was and it was nothing short of spectacular during my 3 visits to this place while staying at the hotel. I was treated to perfectly blended drinks, a wonderful staff who ensured my girl and I were never without a cocktail, and the food was divine. Came here for a team lunch one afternoon. The views outside were awesome, but the musty carpets and the service were not. It was excruciatingly slow. We did have a large group but the rest of the restaurant was pretty much empty, and we ended up spending 2.5 hours there.  To start, we had the buffalo wings (these were fine), and the guacamole. We tried to order two orders, but they said they only had enough for one order. That seemed odd to me, especially since they had avocado toast on the menu, but we still stuck with it. Out comes the guac, which was this unsightly, almost electric green color. It looked like they added food coloring to it, and if not, they definitely bought it premade (which would make sense when they said they ran out). Not surprisingly, it did not taste good.  For my entree, I went with the asparagus risotto (arborio rice, roasted asparagus, parmesan cheese) with chicken. No complaints here. The risotto was perfectly cheesy, and the chicken was cooked just right.  I would say come here for the views and maybe a drink, but you can skip the food.
